<item>
            <title>[PIG-2458] Can&apos;t have spaces in parameter substitution</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2458</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I believe that there is a regression. We can no longer do the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;bin/pig -x local -p THING=&quot;other thing&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;as is, I can&apos;t seem to escape this to make it work, either, which is worse than in the other issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am testing a patch that should fix this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
